
a) Configure Email using UiPath (Gmail/Outlook)
🔸 Using Gmail

Step 1: Open UiPath Studio → Create Blank Process
Step 2: Go to Manage Packages → Install UiPath.GSuite.Activities

Step 3: Drag Use Gmail activity
Step 4: Click Sign In
Step 5: Select your Gmail account and allow permissions

Step 6: Inside Use Gmail, add email activities (Read, Send, etc.)
Step 7: Run the workflow

🔸 Using Outlook

Step 1: Install UiPath.Mail.Activities package
Step 2: Drag Use Outlook 365 or Outlook Application Scope

Step 3: Configure account (if required)
Step 4: Add email activities inside the scope
Step 5: Run the workflow

b) Read Emails

Step 1: Drag Use Gmail or Use Outlook 365

Step 2: Inside it, drag Get Mail Messages activity

Step 3: Configure:

MailFolder → "Inbox"
Top → e.g., 5

Step 4: Create variable mailList (List of MailMessage)

Step 5: Drag For Each activity
Step 6: Set TypeArgument → MailMessage
Step 7: Input → mailList

Step 8: Inside loop, drag Message Box
Step 9: Enter:

item.Subject

Step 10: Run the workflow

c) Send Email with Attachment

Step 1: Drag Use Gmail or Use Outlook 365

Step 2: Inside it, drag Send Mail activity

Step 3: Set:

To → "example@gmail.com"
Subject → "Test Email"
Body → "This is an automated email"

Step 4: In Attachments field, add file path
Example:

"C:\Users\YourName\Documents\file.pdf"

Step 5: Run the workflow

d) Save Email Attachments

Step 1: Drag Use Gmail / Use Outlook 365

Step 2: Drag Get Mail Messages

Step 3: Store output in mailList

Step 4: Drag For Each loop
Step 5: Input → mailList

Step 6: Inside loop, drag Save Attachments activity

Step 7: Set:

MailMessage → item
FolderPath → "C:\Attachments"

Step 8: Run the workflow

e) Reply to Email

Step 1: Drag Use Gmail / Use Outlook 365

Step 2: Drag Get Mail Messages
Step 3: Store in mailList

Step 4: Drag For Each loop

Step 5: Inside loop, drag Reply to Mail Message activity

Step 6: Set:

MailMessage → item
Body → "Thank you for your email"

Step 7: Run the workflow
